results.name: Coefficients of (q*(j(q)-1728))^(1/3) where j(q) is the elliptic modular invariant.
comment: In general, the expansion of (q*(j(q)-1728))^m, where j(q) is the elliptic modular invariant (A000521), and m <> 0, is asymptotic to exp(4*Pi*sqrt(m*n)) * m^(1/4) / (sqrt(2) * n^(3/4)) if 2*m is the positive integer, else is asymptotic to 2^(2*m) * 3^(4*m) * Pi^(2*m) * exp(2*Pi*(n-m)) / (Gamma(-2*m) * Gamma(3/4)^(8*m) * n^(2*m + 1)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 07 2018
mathematica: CoefficientList[Series[((256/QPochhammer[-1, x]^8 + x*QPochhammer[-1, x]^16/256)^3 - 1728*x)^(1/3), {x, 0, 20}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 07 2018 *)
